<item>
            <title>[LU-8576] test-framework.sh is hard coded with o2ib0</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8576</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If you specify NETTYPE=o2ib the &quot;o2ib0&quot; is used always. There is no way to use &quot;o2ib1&quot; for testing. The issue is in h2o2ib() function which hard code this name.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;h2o2ib() {&lt;br/&gt;
        h2name_or_ip &quot;$1&quot; &quot;&lt;font color=&quot;red&quot;&gt;o2ib&lt;/font&gt;&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;br/&gt;
declare -fx h2o2ib&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
